<section id="URL_Paths" remap="TID_30348">
	<title>URL Paths</title>
	<para>
		The recommended convention for URLs is to use alternative collection or resource path segments, relative to the API entry point as described in the following example:
	</para>
	<informaltable>
		<tgroup cols="2">
			<colspec align="left" />
			<colspec align="left" />
			<thead>
				<row>
					<entry>
						URL
					</entry>
					<entry>
						Description
					</entry>
				</row>
			</thead>
			<tbody>
				<row>
					<entry>
						/api
					</entry>
					<entry>
						The REST API Entrypoint
					</entry>
				</row>
				<row>
					<entry>
						/api/v<literal>Version</literal>
					</entry>
					<entry>
						The REST Entrypoint for a specific version of the REST API
					</entry>
				</row>
				<row>
					<entry>
						/api/:collection
					</entry>
					<entry>
						A top-level collection
					</entry>
				</row>
				<row>
					<entry>
						/api/:collection/:id
					</entry>
					<entry>
						A specific resource of that collection
					</entry>
				</row>
				<row>
					<entry>
						/api/:collection/:id/:subcollection
					</entry>
					<entry>
						Sub-collection under the specific resource
					</entry>
				</row>
			</tbody>
		</tgroup>
	</informaltable>
</section>